
  Constantly seeks to direct the company towards expansion to new markets, new products/services, etc, to fuel the company’s future growth.
  build relationships with clients to establish new contracts
  Commercial managers develop risk assessments and pricing structures for products to work toward commercial efforts. Financial planning and budgeting is an important aspect of this job.
  Commercial managers are responsible for overseeing staff, suppliers, and contractors to ensure that deadlines are met. If issues arise with contractors, commercial managers work with them to resolve the problem as quickly as possible so as not to affect the schedule.
  performing tasks both office management and quotation for ship repairs and team coordinator in such repairs like welding works, cleaning, main engine repairs, cargo load test, etc
